						{ Nemo vnq[uam] satis potuit: aut seri&ograve; voluit, quantum
						potuit. Satis ben&egrave; nullus vnq[uam] dixit,
						aut fecit.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position place="left_margin" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						Vt pra[e]stantiori adhuc
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
				<position place="intext" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						opus Sit Natura, arte, exercitatione:
						omnin&oacute;q[ue] industria absoluta.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				No one ever did enough, or wanted seriously enough as much as he could.
				No one ever said anything well enough or did well enough.
				Just as it be necessary for him who most excels to use natura, art, and exercise,
				and total industriousness completely. 
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
