						Fato Prudentia maior.
					</marginalia_text>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Prudence is greater than fate.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
		<marginalia hand="Italian">
			<language ident="LA">
				<position place="tail" book_orientation="0">
					<marginalia_text>
						Alij acuere possunt; non possunt la[e]dere.
						Virescit vulnere virtus. Vincit, qui patitur.
						Omnes actiones, passionesq[ue] Nuga[e], pra[e]ter vnu[m]
						Hoc. Proprium quarto modo, Meum Hoc.
					</marginalia_text>
					<X-ref person="Aulus Furius Antias" book_title="Unknown" language="LA" text="Virescit Vulnere Virtus"/>
					<emphasis method="pen" type="straight" text="Proprium quarto modo"/>
					<emphasis method="pen" type="straight" text="Meum Hoc"/>
				</position>
			</language>
			<translation>
				Others are able to stir up, but they cannot harm.
				'Virtue grows with wounds'. He who suffers, wins.
				All actions and passions are trifles, except this one.
				This is my proper fourth way; this is my own.
			</translation>
		</marginalia>
		
